Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.67,0:00:18.03,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, are you awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.69,0:00:20.45,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,I'm Prince Arnold's aide, Oliver.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.68,0:00:23.29,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Y-Yes! Just a moment, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.43,0:00:29.20,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.20,0:00:30.67,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.88,0:00:34.53,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,This is the only time I could manage \Nto get away from the prince's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.59,0:00:37.76,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, you haven't managed any rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.18,0:00:40.30,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,I'm better off than others are.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.30,0:00:43.58,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold hasn't managed even a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.09,0:00:47.77,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,He's been hard-pressed to complete the work \Nthat accumulated while he was away in Hermity.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.34,0:00:50.40,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I feel I should apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.65,0:00:51.43,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.88,0:00:54.40,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,The prince said he had no intention to marry,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.77,0:00:57.50,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,but through these events,\Nhe's found a lady to be his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.18,0:01:04.87,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please look as much as you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.10,0:01:06.19,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.19,0:01:08.54,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You were examining me, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.76,0:01:11.76,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,My apologies! That was terribly rude of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.50,0:01:16.13,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Your insight is just as keen \Nas the prince said it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.13,0:01:20.64,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Master Oliver, your worry for \NHis Highness truly is heartfelt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:23.26,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Have you been with him long?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.26,0:01:24.67,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,It's been ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.16,0:01:27.60,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,If you've served him for that long,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.98,0:01:32.48,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,then would you know why he \Nhas decided to marry me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.75,0:01:36.94,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Well, to be honest, I'm \Nsurprised by it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.68,0:01:41.24,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,However, I've never seen the prince so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.62,0:01:45.33,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,When he's with you, Lady Rishe, \Nhis smile is so honest and open.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.33,0:01:48.33,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I feel I'm being treated as some sort of toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.77,0:01:51.79,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He isn't denying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.41,0:01:54.64,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,I didn't mean to get \Nabsorbed in conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.64,0:01:59.30,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,His Highness asked me to bring you a list of \Nthe honored guests for the wedding ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.77,0:02:01.68,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.68,0:02:04.86,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Princess Harriet of Siguel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.86,0:02:08.65,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Duke Jonal will be in attendance \Nto represent the Kingdom of Domana.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.65,0:02:11.59,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,And Prince Kyle of Coyolles...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.07,0:02:15.58,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,And this is a list of attendees \Nfor the party tomorrow evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:19.42,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,The party?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.09,0:04:07.57,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Um, Miss Diana, where do these go?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.57,0:04:11.00,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Go and line them up the way I \Nshowed you yesterday please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.00,0:04:11.57,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.57,0:04:13.27,main,Diana,0,0,0,,I'm in the middle of something right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.84,0:04:20.07,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.07,0:04:23.54,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness, may I have \Na moment of your time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.54,0:04:24.36,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.25,0:04:32.79,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold, I've come \Nto beg something of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.79,0:04:35.79,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You did tell me to think \Nof something, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.21,0:04:38.12,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,Think of something you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.00,0:04:41.87,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,My agreement not to lay a finger on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.87,0:04:44.22,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,This time, I truly did break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.72,0:04:48.88,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Would it be possible to leave the \Nselection of my maids to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.88,0:04:51.59,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You can do as you like with that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.46,0:04:58.77,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It seems Oliver didn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:01.31,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,This party tonight...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.31,0:05:05.02,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's meant to say, "The crown prince is \Nlooking for someone to marry from the empire."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.02,0:05:08.74,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's a pointless pretense\Nheld to keep up appearances.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:10.04,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.04,0:05:14.80,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,in this country, I am the crown \Nprincess only as a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.73,0:05:18.93,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,However, I find no dishonor in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.20,0:05:21.21,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.91,0:05:24.53,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,feel free to formally reveal \Nyour fiancée at the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:30.71,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I suppose I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.71,0:05:33.47,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Especially as I've received \Nyour permission to touch you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.47,0:05:36.33,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Well, we are both wearing gloves after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.89,0:06:00.06,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This seems to be a much grander \Nevent than I'd anticipated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.06,0:06:02.25,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,This is still on the smaller side.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:04.30,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,The standards of a large \Ncountry are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.72,0:06:06.42,main,noble 1,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:09.78,main,noble 1,0,0,0,,I was honored to receive an \Ninvitation to attend this evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.78,0:06:11.93,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.19,0:06:16.68,main,noble 2,0,0,0,,Your Highness, please tell my \Ndaughter stories of your travels.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:20.69,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, there aren't any points \Nworth speaking of on their own,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.22,0:06:24.50,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,but I did find good fortune on my trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.02,0:06:29.07,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,As you can see, I've found \Nsomeone to be my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.03,0:06:31.28,main,girl 2,0,0,0,,Did he say wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.28,0:06:33.08,main,girl 1,0,0,0,,His Highness is smiling!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:36.37,main,girl 2,0,0,0,,But he's never so much as\N glanced in our direction!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.37,0:06:39.62,main,noble 2,0,0,0,,Then, this beautiful lady is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.66,0:06:44.33,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Curiosity, jealousy, ulterior motives...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.33,0:06:48.04,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Compared with having my engagement \Nbroken in front of everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.04,0:06:50.17,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,this feels like nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.65,0:06:54.48,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I am pleased to meet all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:06:57.81,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,My name is Rishe Irmgard Weitzner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.90,0:07:09.32,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,As my future wife has only just arrived from \Nanother country, she has no one to rely on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.32,0:07:11.07,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I would like for you to help her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.07,0:07:13.16,main,noble 1,0,0,0,,Of course we will!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.85,0:07:24.62,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,"Future wife"? There's no need to \Nprovoke the other ladies that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.62,0:07:26.93,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's better to make it \Napparent now, while we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.45,0:07:28.30,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Make what apparent?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.36,0:07:33.14,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The fact that I will protect \Nyou, no matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.83,0:07:35.14,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Protect?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.38,0:07:37.08,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Did he just say "protect"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.08,0:07:38.74,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Arnold Hein?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.20,0:07:42.28,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,The man who killed me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.60,0:07:46.89,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness is probably the \None who is most dangerous to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.89,0:07:48.28,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,In what sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.83,0:07:52.73,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Well, I don't think I could \Nmatch you in swordplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.27,0:07:56.61,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It might be worthwhile for me to \Ntry sparring with you one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.61,0:07:59.00,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I would like that very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.00,0:08:02.04,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,And I know it's asking a lot, but I'd \Nlove to receive training from you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.53,0:08:07.79,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You always reply in ways \Nthat exceed my expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.73,0:08:13.02,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I may learn the attack method behind \Nthat fearsome sword technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.40,0:08:16.80,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,No need to force yourself to dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.58,0:08:21.18,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Oh, but as I'm here anyway, \NI would like to enjoy myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.28,0:08:41.75,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,This closeness...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.97,0:08:44.21,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,It takes me back to that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.51,0:08:55.88,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Perhaps I'll try playing \Na little trick on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.71,0:09:00.26,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,If I take the lead, what will he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.91,0:09:05.41,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Then, what about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.07,0:09:14.32,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He looks like he'd like to say, "No \Nmatter what you do, it's no use."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.58,0:09:26.67,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He's so close, but he hasn't \Ncrossed over into my space at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.67,0:09:32.42,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.98,0:09:35.01,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it, he's been...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:40.93,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,No. Back then, too, the whole time, he was...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.82,0:09:56.90,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I'm going to fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.31,0:10:07.29,main,noble 1,0,0,0,,That was splendid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.29,0:10:09.95,main,noble 2,0,0,0,,The two of you were perfectly \Nin step with each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.95,0:10:12.79,main,noble 1,0,0,0,,It was as though I was \Nwatching a sword dance!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.91,0:10:25.08,main,Cornelia,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.92,0:10:29.27,main,Cornelia,0,0,0,,Your dance earlier was quite lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.27,0:10:31.19,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.19,0:10:33.98,main,Cornelia,0,0,0,,If you'd like, please accept this wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.25,0:10:38.71,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.25,0:10:46.23,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,That's the aroma of crushed red peppers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.23,0:10:48.29,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,To think they'd play pranks with food.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.61,0:10:51.78,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This wine has an unusually striking aroma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.78,0:10:53.54,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's quite intriguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.54,0:10:57.01,main,Cornelia,0,0,0,,Are you displeased with \Nthe wine I've brought you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.78,0:11:06.68,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,As I thought, it has a \Nvery stimulating flavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.00,0:11:11.11,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It makes me very happy to have \Nbeen welcomed in such a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.64,0:11:13.76,main,Cornelia,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.29,0:11:23.31,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,That's spicy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.92,0:11:24.73,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Spicy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.24,0:11:26.31,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.24,0:11:30.00,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This wine has peppers in \Nit. It's a special blend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.36,0:11:33.25,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You should just throw that away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.44,0:11:38.81,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,No. This wine has lost its chance \Nto be enjoyed for its flavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.81,0:11:41.21,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,The least I can do for it is to drink it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.32,0:11:45.53,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What? Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.59,0:11:47.68,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Spicy indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.68,0:11:49.35,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I did say so, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.91,0:11:51.85,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Has this fulfilled your duty to this wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.57,0:11:54.78,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.29,0:11:57.23,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.24,0:12:00.72,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,What were you thinking \Nabout during our dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.72,0:12:01.31,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.72,0:12:05.49,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You were thinking of someone\N other than me, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.46,0:12:16.96,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I can't tell him it was his future self.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.79,0:12:20.38,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I was worried for your health, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.25,0:12:24.59,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.86,0:12:26.79,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You've been wounded there, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.77,0:12:34.53,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,The movement of his left shoulder is \Nslightly clumsier than that of his right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.73,0:12:37.07,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,It was back then, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.52,0:12:46.91,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's an old wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.91,0:12:48.88,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It runs all the way along \Nthe top of my shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:51.32,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,There's a spot where it \Nslightly constricts my skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.47,0:12:55.25,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,How horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.66,0:12:57.88,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,It's a very old scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.23,0:13:02.27,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He was struck with a blade over \Nand over... with killing intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.88,0:13:06.87,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Only a few people know about this scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.87,0:13:09.30,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,And no one has ever guessed at its existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.30,0:13:11.31,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Why do you have a scar like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.06,0:13:16.77,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The night wind has grown colder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.79,0:13:42.40,main,Nichole,0,0,0,,Do you think the lady's \Nmaids will be chosen soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.40,0:13:42.99,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.42,0:13:46.97,main,Nichole,0,0,0,,But with the way things are, \Nwe probably won't be chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.91,0:13:52.43,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Haven't you finished yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.82,0:13:54.64,main,Nichole,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry, Miss Diana!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.64,0:13:55.68,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:13:59.69,main,Diana,0,0,0,,And those sheets this morning\N weren't folded the way I taught you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.69,0:14:03.96,main,Diana,0,0,0,,With skills like that, you'll never be \Nchosen as the crown princess's maids.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.96,0:14:05.12,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.54,0:14:09.24,main,Maya,0,0,0,,You again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.24,0:14:11.40,main,Diana,0,0,0,,I don't know which group you belong to,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.40,0:14:13.49,main,Diana,0,0,0,,but I'm amazed that you have \Nthe time to help others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.02,0:14:16.35,main,Diana,0,0,0,,And all of you, finish that up quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.07,0:14:21.69,main,Diana,0,0,0,,It seems that the tablecloths \Nfor the villa will arrive today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.69,0:14:24.92,main,Diana,0,0,0,,If we help with that, I'm certain \Nwe'll be valued more highly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:27.01,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Let's go. Maya? Laura?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.01,0:14:27.92,main,Maya; Laura,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.30,0:14:34.43,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. We're just so \Nbad at remembering things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.80,0:14:37.97,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You haven't been at the \Npalace very long, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.47,0:14:40.86,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,No one gets everything \Nright in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.73,0:14:45.84,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,And it isn't that Elsie and the \Nothers are unused to doing laundry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.84,0:14:49.74,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,They're completing their work. It's \Njust taking longer, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.74,0:14:52.17,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,In that, Diana is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.17,0:14:54.62,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But the cause of it is very clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.95,0:14:58.75,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Have you heard anything about Miss \NDiana's life from before she came here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.08,0:15:03.05,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I think I heard that she's from a \Nwealthy family that has several shops.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.05,0:15:05.07,main,Nichole,0,0,0,,I've heard that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.07,0:15:09.55,main,Nichole,0,0,0,,But they lost it all because \Nthey went into debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.55,0:15:10.62,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.55,0:15:20.39,main,Diana,0,0,0,,It's sparklingly clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.39,0:15:21.83,main,Diana,0,0,0,,When did that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.83,0:15:23.82,main,Diana,0,0,0,,I wonder who did the cleaning here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.40,0:15:28.08,main,Maya,0,0,0,,And that girl who always turns \Nup uninvited isn't here, is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.08,0:15:29.86,main,Laura,0,0,0,,An upstart newcomer like her?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.86,0:15:31.57,main,Laura,0,0,0,,Of course she wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.57,0:15:36.12,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Indeed. To serve the crown princess, \Nmanners are absolutely essential.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.60,0:15:38.05,main,Nichole,0,0,0,,My heart's pounding. Is yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.05,0:15:38.87,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.87,0:15:41.56,main,Nichole,0,0,0,,What do you think the crown princess is like?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.84,0:15:45.66,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.94,0:16:14.61,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I am Rishe Irmgard Weitzner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.68,0:16:19.06,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.06,0:16:21.56,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I wanted to learn the truth \Nabout your situations,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.56,0:16:24.70,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,and I thought that speaking to you as a \Nfellow maid was the best way to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.38,0:16:28.54,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Now, I will read off some names.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.13,0:16:30.67,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Miss Marguerite.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.96,0:16:31.98,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Miss Elsie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.67,0:16:33.67,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Miss Nichole.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.12,0:16:35.18,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Miss Rosa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.18,0:16:36.21,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Miss Hilde.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.64,0:16:37.75,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Miss Amelia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.33,0:16:41.81,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,These people will be my maids.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.81,0:16:42.53,main,Diana,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.53,0:16:44.56,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I look forward to getting to know you better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.56,0:16:47.17,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Now, everyone whose names \Nhave been called, come to—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.17,0:16:48.98,main,Diana,0,0,0,,But why, Lady Rishe?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.98,0:16:51.00,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Everyone you've chosen is new!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.00,0:16:53.28,main,Diana,0,0,0,,We have more experience as maids!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:53.99,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Disrespectful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.99,0:16:55.08,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.02,0:16:58.40,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Yes, what I am saying is disrespectful!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.40,0:17:01.79,main,Diana,0,0,0,,But please look at our \Nabilities as maids!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.00,0:17:03.37,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Miss Diana.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.37,0:17:04.16,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.57,0:17:07.67,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,As of today, you will no longer \Nhold the position of maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.92,0:17:08.76,main,Diana,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.88,0:17:11.02,main,Diana,0,0,0,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.40,0:17:18.16,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Say, Diana? When you \Nfirst came to the palace,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.16,0:17:20.68,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,can you remember what you \Nhad the most trouble with?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.28,0:17:24.45,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Were you able to complete your work the \Nway you do now right from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.36,0:17:27.69,main,Diana,0,0,0,,No. In the beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.13,0:17:31.02,main,Diana,0,0,0,,it was difficult for me to \Nunderstand how things were done.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.83,0:17:34.69,main,Diana,0,0,0,,I couldn't remember after \Nbeing told only once.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.09,0:17:37.89,main,Diana,0,0,0,,But everyone who had been \Nthere longer was so busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.89,0:17:41.37,main,Diana,0,0,0,,They'd say, "I don't have time to \Nteach you, so watch and remember."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.22,0:17:45.60,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Even so, I've grown into a \Nvery competent maid!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.60,0:17:47.21,main,Diana,0,0,0,,I'm not like those girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.43,0:17:52.30,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You're right. There is one way in which \Nyou are very different from those girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.58,0:17:53.55,main,Diana,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.75,0:17:56.67,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You can read and write.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.61,0:18:02.59,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You were born into a merchant's family \Nand received a good education,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.59,0:18:06.94,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,but there are very few ordinary people \Nwho have had the same sort of education.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.94,0:18:11.69,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,You could write down what those with more \Nexperience told you and read it again later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.32,0:18:14.24,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,But what if you hadn't been able do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.24,0:18:19.78,flashback,Diana,0,0,0,,Go and line them up the way I \Nshowed you yesterday please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.78,0:18:20.65,flashback,Elsie,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.12,0:18:25.37,flashback,Diana,0,0,0,,And those sheets this morning\N weren't folded the way I taught you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.99,0:18:32.65,main,Diana,0,0,0,,When my family went bankrupt, we lost \Neverything. There was no one to protect me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.65,0:18:36.63,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Even so, I made myself into a lady's maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.63,0:18:39.65,main,Diana,0,0,0,,I kept wondering, why \Ncouldn't all of you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.91,0:18:44.26,main,Diana,0,0,0,,But it's because I didn't teach you properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.04,0:18:48.30,main,Diana,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.02,0:18:51.16,main,Diana,0,0,0,,I was the one in the wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.91,0:18:55.51,main,Diana,0,0,0,,I'm really so very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.09,0:18:59.24,main,Nichole,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, Miss Diana is very skilled, \Nand she always works her hardest!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.24,0:19:01.45,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Please don't make her quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.33,0:19:06.91,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Thank you, but it only makes \Nsense that I wasn't chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.15,0:19:08.28,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Miss Diana...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.00,0:19:16.63,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,There's something I'd like to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.28,0:19:22.59,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'd like to make this villa into \Na training ground for new maids.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.96,0:19:27.10,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,While they're learning household skills, \NI'd also like them to learn their letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.76,0:19:30.01,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,If they learn to read and \Nwrite along with their work,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.01,0:19:32.65,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,wherever they go, whatever their situation, \Nit will be an asset to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.32,0:19:38.07,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even if they find they must begin a whole \Nnew life, it's sure to prove useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:43.32,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Diana, I'd like for you to help me \Ncreate their teaching materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.88,0:19:44.98,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.25,0:19:49.42,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Even though I said all of \Nthose disrespectful things?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.49,0:19:52.37,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Why, whatever could you be speaking of?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.80,0:19:54.63,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Will you help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.63,0:19:57.69,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Yes, it would be my pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.40,0:20:01.55,main,Albert,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.83,0:20:03.52,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Is it as you predicted?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.52,0:20:04.50,main,Albert,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.04,0:20:08.12,main,Albert,0,0,0,,Though I did think she'd \Ncreate some sort of havoc.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.12,0:20:12.19,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Showing your amusement too openly is \Ndisrespectful toward your future wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.43,0:20:15.76,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Though, I may end up \Nenjoying myself as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.76,0:20:19.66,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,wondering what sorts of things she \Nwill accomplish in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.66,0:20:20.48,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Oliver.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.54,0:20:26.30,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I didn't bring Rishe here to be my wife to \Nbenefit the imperial family or the nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.29,0:20:30.83,main,Diana,0,0,0,,As for the first words they'll learn, what \Ndo you think about cleaning implements?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.32,0:20:33.11,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Since they're used every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.11,0:20:36.58,main,Diana,0,0,0,,I thought everyone might be able to \Nsee how useful it is to memorize them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.58,0:20:38.96,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes, I think that's a very good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.96,0:20:40.30,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.05,0:20:42.42,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.42,0:20:47.51,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Thinking of the best ways to \Nteach everyone is so much fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.71,0:20:49.35,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.03,0:20:52.27,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.49,0:20:54.77,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, you must get ready soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.77,0:20:55.69,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.12,0:20:58.20,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Then, I'll take my leave here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.20,0:20:59.26,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.98,0:21:04.56,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Oh, Miss Diana? After dinner, \Nwill you help me study some more?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.56,0:21:05.49,main,Diana,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.78,0:21:07.29,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.46,0:21:11.74,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,What a lovely dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.08,0:21:14.19,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's the most valuable one I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.86,0:21:17.73,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Will you help me put up my \Nhair in a style to match?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.73,0:21:18.45,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Yes, my lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.35,0:21:24.24,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Um, I've heard that your guest is a merchant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.24,0:21:27.93,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Is your most valuable dress really necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.93,0:21:32.50,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Well, it's one potential ingredient, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.50,0:21:33.93,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Ingredient?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.93,0:21:39.94,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,After all, these are the people who drilled \Nwhat it is to be a merchant into me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.24,0:21:45.19,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,If I can gain them as allies, then my choices\N moving forward increase dramatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.82,0:21:49.16,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,The Aria Trading Company has \Nonly just been established.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.16,0:21:52.00,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,A business negotiation with the \Nimperial family of Galkhein...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.00,0:21:54.95,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,that's something they should want \Nto be successful, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.54,0:22:03.96,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Would dressing more gaudily make me seem \Nmore like a mark who loves to spend money?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.18,0:22:06.15,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I think it's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.15,0:22:09.53,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Putting your hair in a bun with some \Ntrailing tendrils would give you a refined air.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.53,0:22:11.59,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I feel it would match this dress better.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.59,0:22:13.40,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you, Elsie.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.40,0:22:16.07,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,But this outfit is for my battle today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.07,0:22:17.48,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.43,0:22:19.98,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,Your guest has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.53,0:22:28.09,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Allow me to congratulate you \Non your upcoming nuptials.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.67,0:22:34.58,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I am Kaine Tully, from \Nthe Aria Trading Company.
